  "text": "The transition to wholesale competition was most likely to occur in regions where the average cost of generation was above marginal cost, such as the North-East, Illinois, Texas, California, and Montana [CITATION_1] . Regions with comparatively low electricity rates at the end of 1990s, such as the South-East or the North-West largely resisted restructuring efforts.",
